Small blog written in Ruby (Sinatra, Haml+Sass, Activerecord)

How to run: (process will be improved soon)
  1) In project directory run 
    # rake gems:install
     This target will install project dependencies (rack-0.9.1, haml-0.2.7)
  2) Install rmagick 
      on Fedora
      # sudo smart install ruby-RMagick
      
      on Debian/Ubuntu
      # sudo apt-get install libmagick9-dev
      # sudo gem install RMagick
  3) Run rake gallery:fill 'path to folder with images' to fill gallery
  2) Install sinatra from git repository (It's old version in gems)
    # git clone git://github.com/sinatra/sinatra.git
    # cd sinatra
    # rake install (There can be some ruby error, run with --trace, find errorneous line no. in Rackefile and delete this line)  
  3) Adjust database connection parameters in configuration.rb
  4) Create database blog_development and run 
    # rake db:create to init schema
  5) Run to start up server. Site should be available on http://localhost:4567
    # ruby main.rb
  